column10:
[h1]Let's hope for DDS 2 :sadface:[/h1]

[b]Along with the "end game" updade comes my last review for DDS. I give up. I would love to like it, I wish we could have a neutral option on Steam.[/b]

[b](+)[/b] Better graphics than the previous versions of the game;
[b](+)[/b] Won't lie, I could feel an overall improvement (new areas, new events, new missions, money laundering is ok now, etc), but it's still missing better mechanics; maybe in DDS 2;

[b](-)[/b] New updates didn't add much; didn't fix problems or didn't care about fixing them or changing things done wrong; basically decoration  (we just need bed/sofa, clothes wardrobe and table. Am I wrong?);
[b](-)[/b] The game becomes boring and repetitive as you level up (more customers, territories, missions) and do not realize this evolution, because you need to run like crazy from side to side (dealers just ask more quantities, don't help in any way);
[b](-)[/b] No need for recipes, just buy and sell drugs as it is. Game should explore it more, much more. Those guides out there? Waste of time and brains; 
[b](-)[/b] Inventory management is the most annoying thing that I had see in games. EVER.
[b](-)[/b] And many other things that makes no sense (and me sad/angry): farming is useless; AI is dumb and get stuck or frozen in place (I noticed much less AI people walking in the streets now. Why?); we still can't move jars unless it's empty; lack of instructions or descriptions (like how much grams a large jar has?); who the hell close all the gates that we had picked minutes ago?; you lose respect like if you're a child selling candies; never saw a graffiti disappears so fast in my life; and last, but not least, why is this game so DARK? and no options in the settings?

I would love to recommend your game, Mr. CLAUD10 50LANO (who back there in 2020 answered me gently on Steam), but there're things that breaks it to me, or angry me (or make my OCD and anxiety even worse).
I'm sincerely looking forward for DDS 2; hoping that things come out better.
